The paper discusses the use of distillation in deep reinforcement learning, specifically in the context of the Proximal Policy Optimization algorithm. This makes it likely to fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY).
